headline: Where Will Palantir Technologies Stock Be in 10 Years?
summary: Palantir Technologies (NASDAQ: PLTR) went public in September 2020, and shares of the software platforms and data analytics provider have jumped an impressive 714% since then as of this writing, though it is worth noting that almost all of the stock's gains have arrived in the past couple of years following the launch of its artificial intelligence (AI) software platform in April 2023.  Palantir's recent slide is because of factors outside of the company's control.  The broader stock market negativity triggered by the tariff-induced global trade war has led investors to press the panic button.

headline: Stock Market Crash: Is Palantir a Buy?
summary: Palantir Technologies (NASDAQ: PLTR) has not been spared from the recent stock market crash, with the stock trading down roughly 29% from its highs as of this writing.  One of the ongoing oddities about Palantir is that most investors don't know what the company actually does.  Since then, it has developed an artificial intelligence (AI) platform that is meant to be used as an (AI) operating system where users can connect digital assets with their real-world counterparts to apply AI to real-world problems.

headline: Should You Forget Palantir and Buy This Artificial Intelligence (AI) Stock Instead?
summary: Palantir Technologies (NASDAQ: PLTR) has been one of the hottest artificial intelligence (AI) stocks on the market in the past couple of years, registering stunning gains of more than 820%, as of this writing, on the back of the company's rapidly improving credentials in the lucrative market for AI chips.  What's worth noting is investors who bought Palantir a couple of years ago now hold fat gains despite the recent slide.  Palantir's pullback owing to the tariff-fueled turmoil could entice growth investors to add more of this software specialist's shares.
